description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic innovative, flexible and well-motivated physiotherapist to join the Integrated Rehabilitation Team based in East Cornwall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver physiotherapy in the East Cornwall locality to individuals with a Primary Physical Health condition in variety of ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Launceston and Liskeard Community Hospitals – GP-led 18-bedded and 44-bedded rehabilitation units working as part of a team of Occupational Therapy, Physiotherapy, Nursing and Therapy support workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Rehabilitation Team – within the person’s home environment and intervention targeted at a wide variety of conditions, eg long-term, neurological, orthopaedic, falls, frailty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate Care – A more urgent service and working closely with the Home First/Early intervention team in the most appropriate environment for the individual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Integrated Rehabilitation Therapy team works closely with Specialist Therapy teams and is part of the East Cornwall Locality integrated Care Team working with Community Nursing, Social Care, Volunteer and Mental Health teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Within your role of Band 5 Physiotherapist you will be expected to provide supervision for support staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It will be an expectation of this post that the person works flexibly across all areas of care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being able to drive and having access to a vehicle are essential for this post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular clinical supervision will be provided and continuing professional development encouraged. We would welcome informal visits to the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seven day working may be a requirement of this post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details/informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Hyde, Occupational Therapy Team Lead and Interim Physiotherapy Team Lead on 01579 373570&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
